{"title": "Running on the Spot", "content": "In many cartoons, especially ones by Hanna-Barbera, whenever a character starts running, they usually run on the spot for a few seconds before running away. It doesn't matter what they're running from, or why, but they always do this. A Wheel o' Feet is usually applied to this. It's common for this animation to be accompanied by about four seconds of \"wacky\" percussive sound effects followed quickly by a \"slingshot\" zip (perhaps best onomatopoeized as \"Whamma-lamma-bamma-ramma-zamma-whamma-lamma-bamma-ramma-zamma-zamma - ZING!\").", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RunningOnTheSpot", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/HannaBarbera", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SonicTheHedgehog", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PaperMario", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MarioAndLuigi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/ScoobyDoo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/RobotChicken", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SuperMarioWorld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/ChipNDaleRescueRangers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Animalympics", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheFlintstones", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/FamilyGuy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/EdEddNEddy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TerryPratchett"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WheelOFeet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SayingSoundEffectsOutLoud", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OffLikeAShot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Videogame/SonicCD", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Videogame/SuperMarioRPG", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Mook", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeconstructedTrope", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeconstructionCrossover", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeconstructedTrope", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SwallowedWhole", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WheelOFeet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Discworld/Hogfather", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CommediaDellArte"]}